arts.ttl: Leeds United man surely livid with Daniel Farke after double-decision today
arts.sum: Leeds United were pegged back late on at home to Blackburn Rovers in a 1-1 draw, following Pascal Struijk’s penalty to take the lead. Up first for the Whites in the new year was a testing home fixture against Blackburn Rovers, one of three sides to have claimed victory against Leeds this season.

arts.ttl: Daniel Farke pinpoints Leeds United flaw in frustrating Blackburn display
arts.sum: Leeds have chances to win the game, but with Blackburn defending resolutely, Farke was disappointed that they didn not create more. Daniel Farke felt Leeds United were too slow in their approach against Blackburn Rovers in the 1-1 New Year's Day draw - but credited the visitors for stifling their attacking impetus.

arts.ttl: Leeds held by Blackburn after late drama at Elland Road
arts.sum: Danny Batth's last-minute equaliser clinched Blackburn a 1-1 draw at Elland Road and denied Leeds a 10th straight home win.
